              "id": "0116e8ae-5904-3532-bd08-989509d28798",
              "name": "\"Code Injection Vulnerability Detected\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Dangerous code evaluation detected. Executing dynamic code from user input can lead to code injection\" is a security vulnerability in JavaScript programming language. This vulnerability occurs when an application uses untrusted data in the code that it executes. This can lead to malicious code injection, where an attacker can inject and execute arbitrary code within your application, leading to a variety of attacks such as data theft, data corruption, denial of service, etc.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, avoid executing dynamic code as much as possible. If it's absolutely necessary, ensure that the user input is properly sanitized and validated before using it in your code. \n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nIf you're using the `eval()` function in JavaScript, consider replacing it with safer alternatives. For example, if you're using `eval()` to parse JSON data, you can use `JSON.parse()` instead.\n\n```javascript\n// Vulnerable code\nvar obj = eval('(' + userInput + ')');\n\n// Fixed code\nvar obj = JSON.parse(userInput);\n```\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Cheat Sheet on Injection Prevention](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Injection_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-94: Improper Control of Generation of Code ('Code Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/94.html)\n\nPlease note that the provided links are active and accessible for anonymous users at the time of writing this report."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-94",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/94.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-94"
                ]
              }
