            {
              "id": "0898d979-f478-333e-b280-2a37e9d0431b",
              "name": "Potential ReDoS Vulnerability Due to RegExp() Function Argument 'c' in Application: Consider Using Hardcoded Regexes, Input Validation, or Regex Checking/Sanitization Libraries for Security.",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe provided JavaScript code has a potential Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) vulnerability due to the use of the `RegExp()` function. ReDoS is a type of Denial of Service attack where a regular expression (or RegExp) can cause the program to enter an extreme situation, causing it to work very slowly. This can happen when the RegExp used is vulnerable to catastrophic backtracking.\n\nIn this case, the `RegExp()` function is used with a variable argument 'c', which can be manipulated to cause the application to slow down or even freeze, leading to a denial of service.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, consider the following:\n\n1. Avoid using the `RegExp()` function with user-supplied input. Instead, use hardcoded regular expressions whenever possible.\n2. Validate and sanitize input before using it in a regular expression. This can prevent malicious input from causing a ReDoS attack.\n3. Use libraries that can check or sanitize regular expressions to prevent ReDoS vulnerabilities.\n\n## Code Fix Recommendation\n\nThe specific vulnerability sink in the provided code is the use of `RegExp()` function with the argument 'c'. A potential fix could be to validate and sanitize 'c' before using it in the `RegExp()` function. However, without the full context of the code, it's hard to provide a specific fix.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code seems to be obfuscated and it's hard to determine the exact library dependencies. However, it seems to reference `SyntaxHighlighter` and `XRegExp`, so these might be required for the code to execute properly.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP ReDoS](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/Regular_expression_Denial_of_Service_-_ReDoS)\n- [CWE-400: Uncontrolled Resource Consumption](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/400.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-1333",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1333.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-1333"
                ]
              }
