            {
              "id": "0a3a113d-9558-32cd-b1c0-ccab96d51e78",
              "name": "\"Replace `math/rand` with `crypto/rand` due to Security Vulnerability\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nIn Go programming language, the `math/rand` package is used for generating pseudo-random numbers. However, it is not suitable for generating random numbers in a security-sensitive context, as it uses a deterministic source to generate random numbers. This means that if an attacker can predict the seed value, they can predict the sequence of random numbers generated by `math/rand`.\n\nOn the other hand, `crypto/rand` package generates random numbers from sources that a cryptographic algorithm deems as unpredictable, making it suitable for generating random numbers in a security-sensitive context.\n\nUsing `math/rand` instead of `crypto/rand` in a security-sensitive context is a security vulnerability.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, replace `math/rand` with `crypto/rand` in your Go code whenever you need to generate random numbers in a security-sensitive context.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nReplace:\n\n```go\nimport \"math/rand\"\n\nfunc generateToken() string {\n    b := make([]byte, 16)\n    rand.Read(b)\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%x\", b)\n}\n```\n\nWith:\n\n```go\nimport \"crypto/rand\"\n\nfunc generateToken() string {\n    b := make([]byte, 16)\n    _, err := rand.Read(b)\n    if err != nil {\n        log.Fatal(err)\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%x\", b)\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `crypto/rand`\n- `fmt`\n- `log`\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP - Insecure Randomness](https://owasp.org/www-community/vulnerabilities/Insecure_Randomness)\n- [CWE-338: Use of Cryptographically Weak PRNG](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/338.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-338",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/338.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
