            {
              "id": "2117afc0-1935-3425-8219-95e0dc641d03",
              "name": "Potential Code Injection Vulnerability through eval() Function",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe provided JavaScript code snippet is vulnerable to a potential code injection attack through the use of the `eval()` function. The `eval()` function in JavaScript is used to evaluate a string of JavaScript code. If an attacker can control the input to the `eval()` function, they can inject arbitrary JavaScript code, leading to a variety of attacks such as Cross-Site Scripting (XSS), data theft, or even remote code execution.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, the use of the `eval()` function should be avoided whenever possible. If dynamic script execution is required, safer alternatives such as `setTimeout()` or `setInterval()` should be used instead. If the use of `eval()` is unavoidable, the input should be properly sanitized to ensure that it does not contain any malicious code.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nThe provided code snippet is obfuscated, making it difficult to provide a specific fix. However, in general, the `eval()` function should be replaced with a safer alternative. For example, if the `eval()` function is being used to parse JSON data, it should be replaced with the `JSON.parse()` function.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet does not appear to have any library dependencies.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [OWASP Code Injection](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/Code_Injection)\n- [CWE-94: Improper Control of Generation of Code ('Code Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/94.html)\n\nPlease note that these links are subject to change and may not be accessible at all times."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-95",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/95.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
