            {
              "id": "48742045-8be0-30ec-97b2-ea3070b7b520",
              "name": "\"Vulnerability in Dynamic Execution with Eval and Function\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nDynamic execution using `eval()` and `Function()` in JavaScript is a vulnerability that arises when a developer uses these functions to execute dynamically generated code. This can lead to serious security issues, as it allows an attacker to inject malicious code into the application, leading to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks, Remote Code Execution (RCE), and other security vulnerabilities.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, developers should avoid using `eval()` and `Function()` to execute dynamically generated code whenever possible. Instead, they should use safer alternatives that do not execute code dynamically, such as `JSON.parse()` for parsing JSON data.\n\nIf the use of `eval()` or `Function()` is absolutely necessary, developers should make sure that the input passed to these functions is properly sanitized and validated to prevent code injection attacks. This can be achieved by using input validation libraries or built-in JavaScript functions.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is an example of a vulnerable code and how to fix it:\n\n**Vulnerable Code:**\n\n```javascript\nvar user_input = req.body.user_input;\neval(user_input);\n```\n\n**Fixed Code:**\n\n```javascript\nvar user_input = req.body.user_input;\n// Use JSON.parse() instead of eval()\nvar parsed_input = JSON.parse(user_input);\n```\n\nIn the fixed code, `JSON.parse()` is used instead of `eval()`. This ensures that the user input is treated as data, not as code to be executed.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Code Review Guide](https://owasp.org/www-pdf-archive/OWASP_Code_Review_Guide_v2.pdf)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-95: Improper Neutralization of Directives in Dynamically Evaluated Code ('Eval Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/95.html)\n- [CWE-94: Improper Control of Generation of Code ('Code Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/94.html)\n\nPlease note that the links provided are active and accessible to anonymous users at the time of writing this report."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-95",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/95.html"
                  },
