            {
              "id": "58e530b2-67f0-3a02-9faf-256ed44270f9",
              "name": "\"Code Injection Vulnerability Detected\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe provided JavaScript code is vulnerable to code injection. Code injection is a security vulnerability that allows an attacker to control the code that is executed by your program. In JavaScript, this often involves functions like `eval()`, `setTimeout()`, `setInterval()`, and `Function()`, which can execute arbitrary strings of code. In this case, the `eval()` function is used, which is a common source of code injection vulnerabilities.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should avoid using the `eval()` function and similar functions that can execute arbitrary strings of code. Instead, use safer alternatives that do not execute code. For example, if you need to parse JSON data, use `JSON.parse()` instead of `eval()`.\n\nIf you absolutely must use one of these functions, make sure to properly sanitize and validate all inputs to the function. This can help prevent an attacker from injecting malicious code.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nThe provided code is obfuscated, making it difficult to provide a specific fix. However, in general, you should replace the `eval()` function with a safer alternative. For example, if the `eval()` function is being used to parse JSON data, you could replace it with `JSON.parse()`. If the `eval()` function is being used to execute a string of code, consider whether this is necessary and if there is a safer way to achieve the same result.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code does not appear to have any library dependencies.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Code Injection](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/Code_Injection)\n- [CWE-94: Improper Control of Generation of Code ('Code Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/94.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
