            {
              "id": "d065b916-363a-334f-9cf9-1f16cad2b49d",
              "name": "Unsecured HTTP Server Detected: Recommend Using 'http.ListenAndServeTLS'",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Unsecured HTTP Server Detected: Recommend Using 'http.ListenAndServeTLS'\" vulnerability in Go programming language refers to the use of an unsecured HTTP server for communication. This can expose sensitive data to potential interception or manipulation by attackers. The `http.ListenAndServe` function in Go starts an HTTP server without any form of encryption, making it vulnerable to such attacks.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to use the `http.ListenAndServeTLS` function instead, which starts an HTTPS server. HTTPS is HTTP over TLS (Transport Layer Security), and it provides encrypted communication and secure identification of the server.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nReplace the `http.ListenAndServe` function with `http.ListenAndServeTLS`. Here is an example:\n\n```go\nerr = http.ListenAndServeTLS(addr, \"cert.pem\", \"key.pem\", sqhttp.Middleware(router))\n```\n\nIn this example, \"cert.pem\" is the file containing the certificate, and \"key.pem\" is the file containing the private key. You need to replace these with your actual certificate and private key files.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- The `net/http` package from the Go standard library.\n- The `sqhttp` package, which is not part of the standard library. You need to import it from its source.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Transport Layer Protection Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Transport_Layer_Protection_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-319: Cleartext Transmission of Sensitive Information](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/319.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
